article.description: Eric Lockett made the first of two free-throw attempts with 6.8 seconds left to give Florida International a 69-68 victory over North Texas on Thursday night.
article.headline: Lockett's late FT pushes FIU past North Texas 69-68
article.linkText: Lockett's late FT pushes FIU past North Texas 69-68
article.story: MIAMI -- Eric Lockett made the first of two free-throw attempts with 6.8 seconds left to give Florida International a 69-68 victory over North Texas on Thursday night. Ryan Woolridge grabbed the defensive rebound from Lockett's second shot at the line, but then missed a layup to end it. Trejon Jacob and Michael Douglas scored 14 points apiece to lead FIU (12-16, 6-9 Conference USA). Lockett finished with 13 points. Woolridge scored 18 points and Tope Arikawe chipped in 12 for North Texas (14-14, 7-8). Tope Arikawe made two free throws and a dunk, Roosevelt Smart hit a 3-pointer to cap a 9-0 run and the Mean Green led 67-66 lead with 3:48 remaining, but after that they made just one free throw. FIU didn't fare much better late. Lockett made just one field goal with 2:51 left before hitting the game-winning free throw to snap the Panthers' three-game skid.
